  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified that price swept out a prior high and is now hanging in a range, classifying the current phase as consolidation.",
    "Step 2: Marked the high (~33.875) and low (~33.125) of the consolidation range as the two boundaries to watch.",
    "Step 3: Anticipated price would trade to one side of the range and look for a setup; observed the low get swept first.",
    "Step 4: Noted that after the sweep of the range low, price broke out through the range high.",
    "Step 5: Dropped down to the hourly chart to confirm the expansion signature — failure swings at the high, a reversal, and then expansion with very shallow retracements into a new high before consolidating again."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "In consolidation, mark the high and low of the range; a sweep of one side followed by a breakout through the other signals the next directional phase. Shallow retracements on the LTF confirm genuine expansion fractally.",
